Employment:  FARE Labs Pvt. Ltd, is a renowned Testing, Research, and Innovation organization based in | from | 2022-2024 | Gurugram, Haryana. Established in the year 1999, our purpose is inspired by Science and we aspire to achieve excellence in whatever we do.  Our cutting-edge Technology helps organizations adhere to the National and Global quality standards and regulations. Our aim is to strive for continual improvement in scientific research and global leadership in the same. Our team of Scientists, Engineers and Managers work tirelessly to innovate the ways we serve customers and partners. CURRENT COMPANY PROFILE  Current working in Autocal Solution Pvt. Ltd. (Vadodara) as a Calibration Engineer from January 2024 to still…  Autocal Solutions Pvt. Ltd. is a Pan India Company with the most competitive focus in the field of Calibration, Validation and HVAC activities. Established in 2002, we have the capability to offer our customers localised support and services when and wherever required, by continuing to expand our laboratory network, we provide support for the growing needs of our customers both nationally and internationally. We have been accredited by NABL as per ISO/IEC 17025:2005 laboratory in Vasai, Pune and Nashik.  Services: Calibration, Validation, PLC Validation, Food Testing, Microbiological Testing, Air Testing & Water Testing. KEY RESPONSIBILITIES  To create a good working environment in the laboratory and to create harmonious inter laboratory working relations.  Preparing requests for purchase of Instrument/Equipment/Reference standards/Reference materials.  To check calibration schedule of laboratory equipment and conduct calibration from NABL accredited lab as required.  To review or verify the current/valid standard methods for calibration.  To check the working or physical condition of equipment (DUC) received for calibration before job order booking.  On the basis of job order received, jobs to be assigned to relevant division/personnel.  Understanding the complete requirement of the calibration procedures before initiating the calibration.  Ensuring safe and proper storage of DUCs throughout the Calibration process.  To prepare the onsite calibration schedule after coordinating with BD Manager.  To perform/assist onsite calibration and maintain records.  To carry out in-house Calibration.  To keep in check on Environment Monitoring of Mechanical Laboratory.  Ensuring maintenance of general cleanliness and safety requirements in laboratory.  To keep in check maintenance of equipment records.  Mechanical Discipline : (On-Site and lab) Calibrations in following parameters: -  Calibration of all classes Weights and Weighing balances as per OIML Standards.  Calibration of Piston Operated Micropipettes, Glassware’s like glass Pipettes and burettes, Measuring Cylinders, Volumetric Flasks and Beakers & Butyrometers.  Calibration of Density Hydrometers & Lactometers.  Calibration of Glass Capillary Viscometers, Kinematic Viscosity of Newtonian Liquids, Flow Cup, Ford Cup &Viscosity Cup.  Calibration of Pressure Gauge (Dial/Digital), Vacuum Pressure Gauge (Dial/Digital), Magnehelic Gauge, Differential Pressure Gauge , Pressure Switch, Pressure Safety Valve , Pressure Transmitter , Differential Pressure Transmitter and U-tube manometer.  Calibration of Tachometers & Other Indicator of RPM Measurement. (Contact and Non-Contact Type).  Calibration of Gas Flow Measurement of Rotameter by Laminar Flow Element Gas Flow Calibrator.  Calibration of Air Flow Measurement of Anemometer by Indeecon Wind Tunnel System Air Velocity Generator.  Calibration of Water Flow (Flow Rate) Measurement in Water pipes Up to 6000 mm pipe dia. by Ultrasonic Water Flow meter.  Calibration of Temperature Sensor , Temperature Transmitter, Temperature Indicator with Sensor, Temperature & Humidity Indicator with Sensor.  Calibration of pH Meter, Conductivity Meter, pH Transmitter, Conductivity Transmitter.  MS-Office  Good Presentation  AUTOCAD  CCC Certificate Father Name Mr. Ram Saran Date of Birth 27/12/1997 Marital status Single Nationality Indian Language Known Hindi & English Hobbies Listen Music & Riding  I hereby declare that the above written particulars are true to the best of my Knowledge and belief. Date: - (SURYA PRAKASH) Place: -.

