 Coordination (Structure–Architecture–Execution)', ' Quantity Optimization & Detailing', ' Team Supervision & Mentoring', ' ETABS', ' SAFE', ' AutoCAD', ' Revit (Basic)', ' Leadership & Team Management', ' Effective Communication', ' Strategic & Analytical Thinking', ' Problem Solving & Decision Making', ' Time Management', ' Conflict Resolution']::text[], '', 'Name: SUSHMA DUTT | Email: sushdutt1909@gmail.com | Phone: +919650893969 | Location: 굗 굙 굘 New Delhi, India', '', 'Target role: Structural Design Engineer | Headline: Structural Design Engineer | Location: 굗 굙 굘 New Delhi, India | Portfolio: https://B.E.', 'B.E | Civil | Passout 2012', '', '[{"degree":"B.E","branch":"Civil","graduationYear":"2012","score":null,"raw":"Graduation |  B.E. in Civil Engineering – NIMS Institute of Technology | New Delhi || Other |  Diploma in Civil Engineering – New Delhi || Other |  Interior Designing – Jija Bai Industrial Training Institute for Women | New Delhi || Class 12 |  Senior Secondary (12th) – CBSE | New Delhi || Class 10 |  Secondary (10th) – CBSE | New Delhi"}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Structural Design Engineer","company":"Imported from resume CSV","description":"Key Responsibilities & Duties | October | 2012-Present |  Structural modelling, analysis, and design of RCC buildings using ETABS and SAFE for gravity, lateral, wind, and seismic loads.  Preparation of design calculations and reports in compliance with IS 456, IS 1893, IS 13920, IS 875, and other relevant IS codes.  Development of complete GFC and construction drawings including slabs, beams, columns, shear walls, staircases, foundations, and retaining structures using AutoCAD.  Reinforcement detailing and coordination of drawings to ensure constructability and site feasibility.  Coordination with architectural, MEP, and execution teams to resolve design clashes and site queries.  Review of architectural drawings and providing structural inputs at planning and design stages.  Handling design revisions based on client comments, site conditions, and value engineering requirements.  Preparation and checking of BOQ-related structural inputs and material quantities.  Responding to RFIs and providing technical clarifications during execution.  Supervision, mentoring, and checking work of junior engineers and drafting staff.  Ensuring timely submission of drawings and design deliverables as per project schedules.  Preparation of basic Bar Bending Schedules (BBS) for slabs, beams, columns, footings, and staircases for quantity estimation and site reference.  Calculation of reinforcement quantities from structural drawings for basic BOQ and material planning.  Coordination with site engineers to clarify reinforcement detailing and bar cut-lengths (basic level).  Checking contractor-provided BBS for general consistency with issued structural drawings (basic checking only)."}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported project details","description":" East Delhi Hub, Karkardooma ||  ESIC Hospital, Visakhapatnam (CPWD – KMV Projects Ltd.) ||  AIIMS Bibinagar, Telangana ||  Guru Jambheshwar University, Moradabad ||  KPC Medical College, Kolkata ||  Adore Group – Gurgaon & Faridabad ||  Leisure Valley Phase-II, Tech Zone 4, Greater Noida ||  Redevelopment of Chennai Egmore Railway Station"}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\sushma dutt-1 (1).pdf', 'Name: Sushma Dutt

