Headline: Structural Design Engineer

Profile Summary: Structural Design Engineer with 12+ years of experience in RCC structural analysis, design, and detailing for residential, commercial, healthcare, and infrastructure projects. Proficient in ETABS, SAFE, AutoCAD, and IS code–compliant design, with strong coordination skills and hands-on support to execution teams.

Career Profile: Target role: Structural Design Engineer | Headline: Structural Design Engineer | Location: 굗 굙 굘 New Delhi, India | Portfolio: https://B.E.

Key Skills:  Structural Analysis & Design (RCC);  ETABS & SAFE Modelling;  IS Codes Compliance;  GFC & Construction Drawings;  Design Coordination (Structure–Architecture–Execution);  Quantity Optimization & Detailing;  Team Supervision & Mentoring;  ETABS;  SAFE;  AutoCAD;  Revit (Basic);  Leadership & Team Management;  Effective Communication;  Strategic & Analytical Thinking;  Problem Solving & Decision Making;  Time Management;  Conflict Resolution

IT Skills:  Structural Analysis & Design (RCC);  ETABS & SAFE Modelling;  IS Codes Compliance;  GFC & Construction Drawings;  Design Coordination (Structure–Architecture–Execution);  Quantity Optimization & Detailing;  Team Supervision & Mentoring;  ETABS;  SAFE;  AutoCAD;  Revit (Basic);  Leadership & Team Management;  Effective Communication;  Strategic & Analytical Thinking;  Problem Solving & Decision Making;  Time Management;  Conflict Resolution

Skills: Communication;Leadership

Employment: Key Responsibilities & Duties | October | 2012-Present |  Structural modelling, analysis, and design of RCC buildings using ETABS and SAFE for gravity, lateral, wind, and seismic loads.  Preparation of design calculations and reports in compliance with IS 456, IS 1893, IS 13920, IS 875, and other relevant IS codes.  Development of complete GFC and construction drawings including slabs, beams, columns, shear walls, staircases, foundations, and retaining structures using AutoCAD.  Reinforcement detailing and coordination of drawings to ensure constructability and site feasibility.  Coordination with architectural, MEP, and execution teams to resolve design clashes and site queries.  Review of architectural drawings and providing structural inputs at planning and design stages.  Handling design revisions based on client comments, site conditions, and value engineering requirements.  Preparation and checking of BOQ-related structural inputs and material quantities.  Responding to RFIs and providing technical clarifications during execution.  Supervision, mentoring, and checking work of junior engineers and drafting staff.  Ensuring timely submission of drawings and design deliverables as per project schedules.  Preparation of basic Bar Bending Schedules (BBS) for slabs, beams, columns, footings, and staircases for quantity estimation and site reference.  Calculation of reinforcement quantities from structural drawings for basic BOQ and material planning.  Coordination with site engineers to clarify reinforcement detailing and bar cut-lengths (basic level).  Checking contractor-provided BBS for general consistency with issued structural drawings (basic checking only).

